      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://saskatoonsymphony.org/temporary/ee72b7fa-bf20-4141-af1c-781d33a905b4",
    "@type": [
      "https://schema.org/CreativeWork"
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasDerivedFrom": [
      {
        "@id": "https://saskatoonsymphony.org/event/a-change-is-gonna-come/"
      }
    ],
    "https://schema.org/text": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "\n\t\t\t\n\n\n7:30PM, Saturday, April 11, 2026\nTCU Place, Sid Buckwold Theatre\n\n\n35 – 22nd Street East\nSaskatoon, SK S7K 0C8\nGoogle Maps Directions\n\n\nSave Your Seats\n\n\n\nSonia Reid\nJanna Sailorconductor\n\n\nThere is nothing like the powerful soulful voice of an R&B diva…and we couldn’t be more thrilled to be creating this new pops concert with Saskatoon’s very own Sonia Reid.\nMaking her SSO debut in 2024, we all knew some magic was happening and we needed to see what could develop.\nBringing Sonia’s powerhouse voice to the music of Whitney, Dion, Aretha, and so much more, we can’t wait to share this soulful night with you!\nAdd this show to your subscription package and save!\n\n\n\t\t"
      }
    ]
  },
