  {
    "@id": "https://saskatoonsymphony.org/temporary/1ee5ead7-43e4-4b81-80a9-7cf9f3e585db",
    "@type": [
      "https://schema.org/CreativeWork"
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasDerivedFrom": [
      {
        "@id": "https://saskatoonsymphony.org/event/teddy-bear-picnic/"
      }
    ],
    "https://schema.org/text": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "\n\t\t\t\n\n\n10:00AM, Friday, April 24, 2026\nNutrien Wonderhub\n\n\n950 Spadina Crescent E\nSaskatoon, SK S7K 3H6\nGoogle Maps Directions\n\n\nRegister\n\n\n11:15AM, Friday, April 24, 2026\nNutrien Wonderhub\n\n\n950 Spadina Crescent E\nSaskatoon, SK S7K 3H6\nGoogle Maps Directions\n\n\nRegister\n\n\n10:00AM, Saturday, April 25, 2026\nNutrien Wonderhub\n\n\n950 Spadina Crescent E\nSaskatoon, SK S7K 3H6\nGoogle Maps Directions\n\n\nSOLD OUT\n\n\n11:15AM, Saturday, April 25, 2026\nNutrien Wonderhub\n\n\n950 Spadina Crescent E\nSaskatoon, SK S7K 3H6\nGoogle Maps Directions\n\n\nRegister\n\n\n\nIf you go down in the woods today, you’re in for a big surprise…the Saskatoon Symphony Core Musicians and Big Bear are having a spring picnic! Bring a stuffie from home and join the fun as we sing and dance to classical music. We’ll be tired little teddy bears when this picnic is over!\nSpecifically designed for your mini-maestro, these parent and child experiences are perfect for your 2- to 4-year-old music lover.\nExplore music through movement, song and dance with SSO musicians. Let the music connect you and your child and send you both on a journey through melody, rhythm, colour, and beautiful sound.\n\n\n\t\t"
      }
    ]
  },
