  {
    "@id": "https://saskatoonsymphony.org/temporary/51508083-68a5-4571-82e7-18701501ebe7",
    "@type": [
      "https://schema.org/CreativeWork"
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasDerivedFrom": [
      {
        "@id": "https://saskatoonsymphony.org/event/james-ehnes-in-recital/"
      }
    ],
    "https://schema.org/text": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "\n\t\t\t\n\n\n7:30PM, Wednesday, May 6, 2026\nSt John’s Cathedral\n\n\n 816 Spadina Crescent E\nSaskatoon, Saskatchewan S7K 3H4\nGoogle Maps Directions\n\n\nSave Your Seats\n\n\n\nJames Ehnes has established himself as one of the most sought-after musicians on the international stage. Gifted with a rare combination of stunning virtuosity, serene lyricism and an unfaltering musicality, Ehnes is a favourite guest at the world’s most celebrated concert halls.\nTo celebrate his 50th birthday, Ehnes is touring across Canada! He stops in Saskatoon to perform a recital at St. John’s Cathedral.\n\n\n\t\t"
      }
    ]
  },
