      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://saskatoonsymphony.org/temporary/fb416511-6418-4298-bfe0-2a0f94c8ead5",
    "@type": [
      "https://schema.org/CreativeWork"
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasDerivedFrom": [
      {
        "@id": "https://saskatoonsymphony.org/event/croon/"
      }
    ],
    "https://schema.org/text": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "\n\t\t\t\n\n\n8:00PM, Monday, July 6, 2026\nThe Broadway Theatre\n\n\n715 Broadway Ave\nSaskatoon, SK S7N 1B3\nGoogle Maps Directions\n\n\nSave Your Seats\n\n\n\nScottish and with a voice like a young Frank Sinatra, the SSO is thrilled to have 19-year-old Michael Lewis making his Canadian debut in a show featuring some of the great crooner hits that the likes of Frank, Dean, and Buble have made us fall in love with. \nMichael has developed a reputation far beyond his years, combining a timeless voice with a natural stage presence that feels both classic and entirely fresh. What began as a quiet fascination — discovering Sinatra through TikTok and singing along in his bedroom — has quickly evolved into a remarkable rise through some of the UK’s most respected stages.\nThere is something strikingly timeless about Michael Lewis. In an era of fast-moving trends, he brings a sense of elegance, storytelling and musicality that harks back to the great crooners, yet feels entirely relevant to today’s audiences. Whether performing in an intimate setting or on a festival stage, he connects with audiences in a way that is rare at any age — and even more so at just 18!\nThis concert is a part of the SaskJazz Festival.\n\n\n\t\t"
      }
    ]
  },
